sec.p:
The initial wet biomass is introduced into an air dryer. Only low-grade heat is needed for air drying [24], which is readily available from the exothermal PBtL process. Therefore, air drying is preferred over steam drying in this study. Additional pre-treatment steps, such as torrefaction or pelleting [25], are not considered in this study, as they are not necessarily required for an SXB gasifier. These steps increase the biomass LHV and subsequently the process yield. This delta in yield would have to be weight against additional investment and operation costs for these pre-treatment steps.
